ArgoCD Installation: 
https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/getting_started/

Get Argo UI
kubectl patch svc argocd-server -n argocd -p '{"spec": {"type": "LoadBalancer"}}'

Initial admin password
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d ; echo

Changing Default Sync Time
The default sync interval in ArgoCD controls how often ArgoCD automatically syncs your applications from Git. By default, this is 3 minutes (180 seconds).

1. Edit ArgoCD ConfigMap
kubectl -n argocd edit configmap argocd-cm

Add the following block at the end:
data:
  timeout.reconciliation: 10s #syncinterval

2. Restart Application Controller
kubectl -n argocd rollout restart statefulset argocd-application-controller

3. Verify Setting
kubectl -n argocd get configmap argocd-cm -o yaml | grep timeout.reconciliation
You should see:
timeout.reconciliation: 10s

ArgoCD now checks your Git repositories every 10 seconds for changes.

